WarNews.message:
Terminid spores have engulfed Heeth and Angel's Venture, spawning hordes of Terminids that overwhelmed our colonial militias. Clearly, the bug hive instinct oriented their mindless expansion towards dishonoring the memory of those who fought to free these planets.

Your fellow Helldivers paid for these lands with their lives. We cannot lose them now. Hold the planets until SEAF reinforcements arrive.

The Advanced Liberation Tools Research Agency (ALTRA) has tested successful prototypes of a new combat asset. Helldivers are advised to review proper mechanical operation procedures in preparation for the incoming asset.

NEW MAJOR ORDER
Tien Kwan is home to the sole arsenal of new Exosuit technology. It is only a matter of time before the Automatons discover the arsenal and steal it for themselves. Liberate Tien Kwan, before it's too late.

AUTOMATON COUNTERATTACK
Intercepted messages indicate bot plans for a significant push. Increased resistance on Automaton planets is anticipated.

Well done, Helldivers. Tien Kwan has been returned to the care of Managed Democracy. The Morgunson Arsenal, and its stockpile of freshly-produced Exosuits, were recovered intact.

The EXO-45 PATRIOT EXOSUIT is now available for requisition.

Upon each Barrier Planet now stands a network of massive, Termicide-dispensing towers: the Terminid Control System. Once activated, the TCS will exterminate every Terminid on that planet, and inoculate it against all future infestations. 

However, surges in Terminid activity have forced the SEAF Engineers to evacuate. Now, only the Helldivers can ensure the safety of our citizens.

The Terminid Control System must be activated—at any cost.

NEW MAJOR ORDER
Activate Terminid Control System

FENRIR III SECURED
The Terminid Control System is now fully activated on Fenrir III.

TURING SECURED
The Terminid Control System is now fully activated on Turing.
The TCS has been fully activated on half of the Barrier Planets.

setting.overrideBrief: Complete the designated number of missions on Cyberstan, to support a ground invasion towards the enemy capital: Transcendence.

Cull the designated Titan-Class Terminids in order to secure egg specimens for fundraising sales to high-value citizens, to fund additional reinforcements and experimental stratagem support for Operation VALID PRETEXT.

biome.description: This arid, rocky biome covering this world has driven the evolution of exceptionally efficient water usage in its various organisms.
The lifeless grey of this planet is interrupted only by the violet flowers that grow from strange, parasitic outcroppings.
A perenially chilly climate has allowed short, colourful shrubs to flourish across this planet's surface.
Scorching temperatures, high winds, and low precipitation cause a near-constant cycle of fires to sweep this planet, punctuated by short bursts of lush rebirth between infernos.

Dense, toxic fumes from deep within the planet's crust seep out of cracks in the earth and coat the ground in a sickly haze.
A crimson algae has propagated wildly across this entire planet, coating its rocky hills with a constant red that masks the spilt blood of the heroes who defend it from tyranny.
Ice and moss-covered rock can be found across most of the surface of this planet.
